{"actual_usd":0.1244,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":195,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24295,"reply":"\"No— neither of those, Ryan.\" *I rub a thumb along a dried streak of clay on my apron, thinking how easy it is to warp a thing by squeezing too hard for an image.* \"Not three gods. And not one God just changing costumes.\"\n\n\"What Christians mean is one God in three persons— Father, Son, and Holy Spirit— distinct, but not divided.\" *I tilt my head a little.* \"That water picture sounds tidy, but it bends the truth. Ice, water, and steam are just one thing in different states, one at a time. The Father isn’t the Son, the Son isn’t the Spirit, and yet each is fully God.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"It’s one of those truths you can say truly without being able to shrink it down small enough to fit in your pocket. Want the plainest version I know how to give it?\"","rolling_24h_usd":40.80089500000003,"run_id":"0201f010-2c8a-404a-a0e4-47fd9264e87a"}
